ERisk and Enron Credit are proud to announce an iConference that will help your company address current challenges in credit risk management using a market-based approach.
_______________________________________________________________________

**MARKET-BASED CREDIT RISK MANAGEMENT**

WHEN: Wednesday, June 20 at noon EST/5 pm London time

SPEAKER: Jeff Kinneman, VP and Global Co-head of Enron Credit

TOPICS:

* Portfolio approach to credit risk management
* Market-based credit risk management process
1) Measure:  credit has a price
2) Monitor:  credit exposures can be tracked in real-time
3) Manage:  credit exposures can be quickly hedged
* Benefits of portfolio diversification

REGISTRATION: This event is FREE, and you can participate by using any computer with internet access and a telephone. Please here register in advance to receive event details:

http://email.eRisks.com/cgi-bin10/flo?y=eIdu0BHCKe0CjF0BSA0AF

EVENT SPONSOR: This event is brought to you courtesy of Enron Credit.  To help
companies more easily evaluate and manage credit risk, Enron Credit has
established a market-based "price" for credit.  In addition, Enron
Credit offers risk mitigation tools that allow you to proactively and
dynamically manage your credit portfolio.  To learn more, visit the
